{"id":"sala","term":"Sala","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A shoot, a descendant of Arphaxed (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 3:35\">Luke 3:35</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 3:36\">36</a>); called also Shelah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:18\">1 Chr. 1:18</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:24\">24</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Luke 3:35","Luke 3:36","1 Chronicles 1:18","1 Chronicles 1:24"]}